== 早年生涯 ==
他的媽媽是[[西班牙人|西班牙人]]而爸爸是[[北愛爾蘭|北愛爾蘭]]人<ref>Editor [http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/technology/colourblind-artist-wants-cyborg-eye-in-irish-passport-28749689.html "Artist wants cyborg eye in Irish passport"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/technology/colourblind-artist-wants-cyborg-eye-in-irish-passport-28749689.html |date=20160807023408 }}, [[Belfast_Telegraph|Belfast Telegraph]], 15 May 2012</ref>，他出生時就患有嚴重的[[色盲|色盲]]，導致他只能看到[[灰階|灰階]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2017/04/worlds-first-cyborg-human-evolution-science/|title=How a Color-Blind Artist Became the World’s First Cyborg|date=2017-04-03|access-date=2017-09-15|archive-date=2019-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116141059/https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2017/04/worlds-first-cyborg-human-evolution-science/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他在[[巴塞隆那|巴塞隆那]]長大並在那裡學習鋼琴<ref>FC "Més de 4000 espectadors ja han vist els Pastorets que acaben diumenge" ''Capgros'' 12–19 February 1999</ref><ref>JV "Alumnes del Campeny representen Terra Baixa" ''Crònica de Mataró'' 16 May 1998</ref>，在11歲時就開始譜曲<ref>Mas, Pere. [http://www.catradio.cat/reproductor/369502 "Neil Harbisson, ciborg de colors"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.catradio.cat/reproductor/369502 |date=20101113153457 }}, ''[[Catalunya_Ràdio|Catalunya Ràdio]]'', 25 August 2009</ref>。16歲時，他在亞歷山大·薩托拉斯研究所（Institut Alexandre Satorras）學習美術，並獲得特別許可，可以不用在作品中使用任何顏色，也因此他早期的作品都是黑白的<ref>Brennan, Ciarán. [http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/health/2008/0527/1211740478000.html "When what you see is not in colour"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/health/2008/0527/1211740478000.html |date=20121021041556 }}, ''[[The_Irish_Times|The Irish Times]]'', 5 May 2008.</ref><ref>[[Bryony_Gordon|Bryony Gordon]]. [http://www.independent.ie/world-news/europe/from-black-and-white-to-colour----eyes-opened-to-sound-of-socks-278060.html "From black and white to colour . . . eyes opened to sound of socks"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.ie/world-news/europe/from-black-and-white-to-colour----eyes-opened-to-sound-of-socks-278060.html |date=20100603201521 }}, ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]'', 13 January 2005.</ref>。

少年時期，他曾為了拯救三棵樹免遭砍伐而在樹上住了幾天<ref>Ferran, Helena. [http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/elpunt/noticia?p_idcmp=-960066 "Un «cyborg» català al Regne Unit"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/elpunt/noticia?p_idcmp=-960066 |date=20190608205838 }}, ''[[El_Punt|El Punt]]'', 5 December 2004.</ref><ref>de la Fuente, Antonia. [http://hemeroteca.lavanguardia.es/preview/2009/01/28/pagina-5/34176112/pdf.html?search=neil%20harbisson "Barones rampantes de Mataró se instalan en árboles para impedir que los corten"], ''[[La_Vanguardia|La Vanguardia]]'', 27 May 2001.</ref>，他的倡議得到了3000多人的支持，他們簽署了一份請願書以保護樹木<ref>"Penjats pels arbres" Front page of ''[[El_Punt|El Punt]]'' 26 May 2001</ref>。經過幾天的抗議，市政廳終於宣布不砍伐樹木<ref>Ferran, Helena. [http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/elpunt/noticia?p_idcmp=-960066 "Famós a Mataró per <<salvar>> arbres"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/elpunt/noticia?p_idcmp=-960066 |date=20190608205838 }}, ''[[El_Punt|El Punt]]'', 5 December 2004.</ref>。

19歲那年，他移居英國，在達丁頓藝術學院學習音樂創作<ref>Martinez Arias, Alberto. [http://www.rtve.es/alacarta/audios/programa/puntos-vista-primer-ciborg-del-mundo-reconocido-por-gobierno/1301325/ "Primer ciborg del mundo reconocido por un gobierno"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rtve.es/alacarta/audios/programa/puntos-vista-primer-ciborg-del-mundo-reconocido-por-gobierno/1301325/ |date=20131204050411 }}, Puntos de Vista,''[[Radio_Exterior_de_España|Radio Exterior de España]]'', 23 January 2012.</ref>。

== 作品 ==
哈維森將他的作品定義為[[賽博格藝術|賽博格藝術]]，設計新感官和新感覺的藝術並與之融合的藝術<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2014/may/06/neil-harbisson-worlds-first-cyborg-artist|title=Neil Harbisson: the world's first cyborg artist|last=Jeffries|first=Stuart|date=2014-05-06|work=The Guardian|access-date=|language=en|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109021533/https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2014/may/06/neil-harbisson-worlds-first-cyborg-artist|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他將自己的創作比喻為雕塑。他的目標是塑造自己的心，以創造對現實的全新的認識<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sciencefriday.com/articles/hearing-color-through-a-cyborg/|title=Hearing Color Through a Cyborg - Science Friday|last=|first=|date=|work=Science Friday|access-date=|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204154008/https://www.sciencefriday.com/articles/hearing-color-through-a-cyborg/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他將[[賽博格藝術|賽博格藝術]]的這一特定分支定義為「感知主義」，一種設計對現實的新感知的藝術，並視之為後藝術運動，因為它的實用性使藝術家、藝術作品、它所存在的空間以及觀眾之間沒有距離。哈維森是藝術家，同時也是藝術作品。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://metalmagazine.eu/en/post/interview/neil-harbisson-the-reality-of-a-cyborg|title=Neil Harbisson, the reality of a cyborg|last=Pristauz|first=Julius|date=1 December 2017|work=Metal Magazine|access-date=|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124011128/https://metalmagazine.eu/en/post/interview/neil-harbisson-the-reality-of-a-cyborg|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 色彩感知 ：賽博格天線 ===
賽博格天線是一種用來擴增色彩感知的傳感系統<ref>Sanchis, Ima. [http://www.lavanguardia.es/free/edicionimpresa/20100710/53961073929.html "La veo en blanco y negro pero la oigo en colores"], La Contra de ''[[La_Vanguardia|La Vanguardia]]'', 10 July 2010.</ref>。它被植入並骨整合到哈維森的頭部，並從他的[[枕骨|枕骨]]內萌發。自2004年起，它就永久固定在哈維森的頭上，使他能夠感覺到並聽到可聽見的振動<ref name="Painting by ear">Harbisson, Neil. [http://www.artinfo.com/news/enlarged_image/27743/96442/ "Painting by ear"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.artinfo.com/news/enlarged_image/27743/96442/ |date=20080803074843 }} ''Modern Painters, The International Contemporary Art Magazine'' pp.70–73. New York, June 2008.</ref>，包括人眼不可見的顏色，例如[[紅外線|紅外線]]和[[紫外線|紫外線]]<ref>Alfredo M. Ronchi: ''Eculture: Cultural Content in the Digital Age.'' Springer (New York, 2009). p.319 {{ISBN|978-3-540-75273-8}}</ref>。它還能連上網路使他能接收來自其他[[傳感器|傳感器]]或[[人造衛星|人造衛星]]的訊號。<ref name="theguardian.com" /> 

哈維森於2003年與亞當·蒙丹頓（Adam Montandon）開始在大學開發天線<ref>Nadotti, Cristina. [http://www.repubblica.it/2005/e/sezioni/scienza_e_tecnologia/daltonismo/daltonismo/daltonismo.html?ref=search "Daltonici, mondo a colori con l'aiuto di "Eye-borg""] {{Wayback|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2005/e/sezioni/scienza_e_tecnologia/daltonismo/daltonismo/daltonismo.html?ref=search |date=20200216025957 }}, ''[[La_Repubblica|La Repubblica]]'', 31 May 2005.</ref>，並由彼得·凱斯（Peter Kese）和馬蒂亞斯·利薩納（Matias Lizana）等人進行了升級<ref name="Painting by ear" />。生物倫理委員會一再拒絕天線植入手術，但其實匿名醫生都在進行<ref>BROKEN LINK Millás, Juan José. [http://www.elpais.com/articulo/portada/ciborg/tercer/ojo/elpepusoceps/20120115elpepspor_9/Tes. "El Cyborg del Tercer Ojo"]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''[[El_País|El País]]'', 15 January 2012.</ref>。

=== 網路感知 ===
哈維森允許五個朋友（[[五大洲|五大洲]]各一個）將顏色，圖像，影像或聲音直接發送到他的頭裡。 如果他在睡著時接收到顏色，他的朋友們就可以著色並改變他的夢境<ref>Williams, Alison [http://www.notimpossiblenow.com/lives/neil-harbisson-not-impossible-cyborg-series "Cyborg Series #1"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20141130083012/http://www.notimpossiblenow.com/lives/neil-harbisson-not-impossible-cyborg-series |date=2014-11-30 }}, ''Not Impossible Now'', 29 October 2014</ref>。[[半島電視台|半島電視台]]的談話節目《The Stream》現場直播了頭骨傳播圖像的首次公開演示<ref>[[The_Stream|The Stream]][http://stream.aljazeera.com/story/201411270009-0024381 "The World's First Cyborg"] {{Wayback|url=http://stream.aljazeera.com/story/201411270009-0024381 |date=20200216033409 }}, ''[[Al_Jazeera|Al Jazeera]]'', 27 November 2014.</ref>。第一個直接撥打電話到他的頭裡的人是Ruby Wax<ref>[Shin, Nara [http://www.coolhunting.com/tech/charged-neil-harbisson "Cool Hunting: Neil Harbisson"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.coolhunting.com/tech/charged-neil-harbisson |date=20180721072608 }}, ''Coolhunting'', 5 May 2014</ref>。

[[File:Color_Concert_by_Neil_Harbisson.jpg|thumb]][[加泰隆尼亞音樂宮|加泰隆尼亞音樂宮]]舉行的「色彩」音樂會 (2014)<ref>Vodafone [https://web.archive.org/web/20140208040131/http://firsts.com/content/vodafone-firsts/home/Neil-Harbisson.html "First color conducted concert"], ''Firsts'', January 2014</ref>|300x300px]]

2014年，哈維森創作了世界上第一幅頭骨傳播的畫。[[時報廣場|時代廣場]]上的觀眾在畫布上繪製簡單的彩色條紋時所發送的顏色，是直接通過互聯網實時接收到哈比森的大腦中的<ref>Jones, Jonathan [https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/jonathanjonesblog/2014/aug/27/cyborg-art-daring-stunt-creativity-future "Will cyborgs turn art into a supersensory futureworld?"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/jonathanjonesblog/2014/aug/27/cyborg-art-daring-stunt-creativity-future |date=20200216031859 }}, ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]'', 27 August 2014.</ref>。他正確地辨認出了相同顏色的條紋，並在距離[[時報廣場|時代廣場]]10街區的《紅門》的觀眾面前的畫布上繪製了相同的顏色<ref>Pearlman, Ellen [http://www.mitpressjournals.org/doi/abs/10.1162/PAJJ_a_00264?journalCode=pajj "I, Cyborg"], ''[[PAJ_(journal)|PAJ (journal)]]'', May 2015</ref>。

=== 時間感知：太陽之冠（Solar Crown） ===
太陽之冠是一種具有時間感知功能的感覺裝置。一個旋轉的熱點每24小時繞行哈維森的頭部一次<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://metalmagazine.eu/en/post/interview/neil-harbisson-the-reality-of-a-cyborg|title=Neil Harbisson, Metal Magazine|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2017-12-03|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124011128/https://metalmagazine.eu/en/post/interview/neil-harbisson-the-reality-of-a-cyborg|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。當他感覺到熱點在額頭時，這表示現在是倫敦的正午時分（經度0°），當熱點到達他的右耳時，則是[[紐奧良|紐奧良]]的正午時分（緯度90°）<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elespanol.com/ciencia/investigacion/20170627/226977715_0.html|title=Así suenan los colores para Neil Harbisson, el 'ciborg' que dejó boquiabiertos a todos en Masterchef|work=El Español|access-date=2017-12-03|language=es|archive-date=2020-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216032620/https://www.elespanol.com/ciencia/investigacion/20170627/226977715_0.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。哈維森的目的是通過製造時間[[錯覺|錯覺]]來將[[愛因斯坦|愛因斯坦]]的時間相對論付諸實踐<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/ciencia/abci-neil-harbisson-pondre-cabeza-organo-para-sentir-paso-tiempo-201706021703_noticia.html|title=Neil Harbisson: "Me pondré en la cabeza un órgano para sentir el paso del tiempo"|last=|first=|date=|work=abc|access-date=|language=es|archive-date=2018-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181117061458/https://www.abc.es/ciencia/abci-neil-harbisson-pondre-cabeza-organo-para-sentir-paso-tiempo-201706021703_noticia.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當他的大腦習慣了時間的熱點在頭上移動的步調時，他將探索是否可以通過改變熱點的旋轉速度來改變對時間的感知<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.techly.com.au/2017/08/25/world-cyborgs-point-of-view-neil-harbisson/|title=See the world from a cyborg's point of view: A chat with Neil Harbisson|last=|first=|date=2017-08-25|work=Techly|access-date=|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228215730/https://www.techly.com.au/2017/08/25/world-cyborgs-point-of-view-neil-harbisson/|archive-date=2019-02-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。哈維森指出，既然我們可以製造[[視覺|視覺]]上的[[錯覺|錯覺]]，是因為我們有眼睛可以感知影像，相同地，如果我們有一個可以感知時間的器官，就應該可以創造出時間上的[[錯覺|錯覺]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noizz.ro/connected/neil-harbisson-urmatorul-pas-in-evolutia-omenirii/336y2s6|title=Următorul pas în evoluția omenirii: tipul ăsta are Internet în craniu, aude culori și acum vrea să simtă Soarele sub piele|last=|first=|date=2017-10-05|work=Noizz.ro|access-date=|language=ro|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204012811/https://noizz.ro/connected/neil-harbisson-urmatorul-pas-in-evolutia-omenirii/336y2s6|archive-date=2019-12-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。如果時間[[錯覺|錯覺]]可行，那麼他將能夠延伸或控制對時間、年齡和時間旅行的感知。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hvmn.com/podcast/episode-40-the-worlds-first-cyborg-ft-neil-harbisson|title=Episode 40: The World's First Cyborg ft. Neil Harbisson {{!}} HVMN Podcast|last=|first=|date=|website=HVMN|language=en|access-date=|archive-date=2019-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724021552/https://hvmn.com/podcast/episode-40-the-worlds-first-cyborg-ft-neil-harbisson|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 齒間通訊系統 ：[[藍牙|藍牙]][[牙齒|牙齒]]（Bluetooth Tooth） ===
齒間通信系統由兩個牙齒組成，每個牙齒包含一個啟用藍牙的按鈕和一個迷你振動器<ref>Vanhalakka, Vesa [https://www.aamulehti.fi/maailma/tama-mies-on-elava-kyborgi-kalloon-ruuvatusta-antennista-on-tullut-osa-hanen-kehoaan-24000985/ "Tämä mies on elävä kyborgi – kalloon ruuvatusta antennista on tullut osa hänen kehoaan"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.aamulehti.fi/maailma/tama-mies-on-elava-kyborgi-kalloon-ruuvatusta-antennista-on-tullut-osa-hanen-kehoaan-24000985/ |date=20171203224551 }}, [[Aamulehti|Aamulehti]], 16 October 2016</ref>。每當按下按鈕時，都會向對方的牙齒發送振動<ref>[https://www.museumnext.com/insight/the-renaissance-of-our-species/ "The Renaissance of our Species"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.museumnext.com/insight/the-renaissance-of-our-species/ |date=20190406150806 }}, Museum Next, New York, November 2016</ref>。一顆牙齒安裝在哈維森的嘴中，另一顆則安裝在[[穆恩·里巴斯|穆恩·里巴斯]]的嘴中。哈維森和里巴斯都知道如何用[[摩斯密碼|摩斯密碼]]進行交流，因此他們能夠在牙齒之間進行交流<ref>Kędzierski, Robert [http://next.gazeta.pl/next/7,156830,21687126,czlowiek-przyszlosci-bedzie-postrzegal-swiat-przez-zmysly-ktore.html "Człowiek przyszłości będzie postrzegał świat przez zmysły, które dopiero stworzymy"] {{Wayback|url=http://next.gazeta.pl/next/7,156830,21687126,czlowiek-przyszlosci-bedzie-postrzegal-swiat-przez-zmysly-ktore.html |date=20200803085903 }}, [[Gazeta.pl|Gazeta]], 2 May 2017</ref>。該系統的首次演示在[[聖保羅|聖保羅]]舉行<ref>Zuin, Lidia [https://killscreen.com/versions/talk-cyborg-activists-neil-harbisson-moon-ribas/ "A talk with cyborg activists Neil Harbisson and Moon Ribas"] {{Wayback|url=https://killscreen.com/versions/talk-cyborg-activists-neil-harbisson-moon-ribas/ |date=20200924212504 }}, [[Kill_Screen|Kill Screen]], 2016</ref>。

