=== 研究 ===
2009年，哈維森根據2004年至2009年在數百種[[人類|人類]][[皮膚|皮膚]]上檢測到的[[色相|色相]]和[[光線|光線]]發布了“人類色輪”<ref name="ara.cat" />。該研究的目的是指出人類不是黑人或白人，而是不同深淺的橙色-從非常深的橙色到非常淺的橙色。<ref>Hadden, Gerry [http://www.theworld.org/2012/02/neil-harbisson-color-eyeborg/ "Color-Blind Artist Neil Harbisson Uses Webcam-Like Eyeborg to ‘Hear’ Color"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theworld.org/2012/02/neil-harbisson-color-eyeborg/ |date=20130828095720 }}, [[The_World_(radio_program)|The World]], [[Public_Radio_International|Public Radio International]], 28 February 2012.</ref>

哈維森在題為“ Capital Colors”<ref>Marković, Stjepan. "Kiborg iz Engleske u Zagrebu 'slusao' boje" ''24 sata Promotivni Primjerak'' Front Page, 17 December 2007</ref><ref>Marković, Stjepan. [http://www.24sata.hr/news/prvi-sluzbeni-covjek-kiborg-cuje-trideset-i-sest-boja/41616/ "Prvi sluzbeni covjek kiborg cuje trideset i sest boja"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.24sata.hr/news/prvi-sluzbeni-covjek-kiborg-cuje-trideset-i-sest-boja/41616/ |date=20100206204952 }} ''[[24_sata_(Croatia)|24 sata]]'' pp.12–13, 17 December 2007</ref>的作品中展示了他所訪問過的不同城市的主色調<ref>Brooks, Richard. [http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/visual_arts/article3423446.ece "Colour-blind artist learns to paint by hearing"] {{Wayback|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/visual_arts/article3423446.ece |date=20080517063723 }}, ''[[The_Sunday_Times|The Sunday Times]]'', 24 February 2008.</ref><ref>Dee, Michael. [http://www.kunstforalle.no/redaksjonelt.asp?meny=6,172,341 "Neil Harbisson – en kunstnerisk kyborg"], ''Kunst for alle'', p.32-35 Issue 3, 2009.</ref>。他掃描每個城市的顏色，直到他能夠用至少兩種[[色相|色相]]表示它。<ref>Bojka [http://www.lupiga.com/vijesti/index.php?id=4932 "Katalonci "čudnim zvukovima" odredili boju Zagreba"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.lupiga.com/vijesti/index.php?id=4932 |date=20130510045316 }} ''Lupiga'', 29 November 2007.</ref><ref>"Zivi sa zicama na vrhu glave" ''[[24_sata_(Croatia)|24 sata]]'' Front Page, 17 December 2007</ref>

== 行動主義 ==
2004年，Harbisson的英國護照續簽被拒絕，因為[[英國護照署|英國護照署]]不允許他帶著電子設備出現在他的頭上，哈維森則回信解釋說，他被認定為[[改造人|改造人]]，因此他的天線應被視為他身上的一個器官而非設備。經過數週的溝通，他的照片終於被接受。<ref>Miah, Andy / Rich, Emma. [https://books.google.com/books?id=382wJB2DPCwC&pg=PA130&dq=%22neil+harbisson&hl=en&ei=GsDlS-iFNceE-Qapx9DoAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22neil%20harbisson&f=false ''The medicalization of cyberspace''], Routledge (New York, 2008). p.130 {{ISBN|978-0-415-37622-8}}</ref><ref name="ara.cat">Serra, Laura [http://www.ara.cat/ara_premium/ara_tu/No-blancs-negres-tots-taronges_0_411558847.html "No som blancs ni negres, tots som taronges"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ara.cat/ara_premium/ara_tu/No-blancs-negres-tots-taronges_0_411558847.html |date=20111008232028 }} ''[[Ara_(newspaper)|Ara]]'', 19 January 2011.</ref>

2011年，在[[巴塞隆那|巴塞隆那]]舉行的一次示威活動中，哈維森的天線被警方損壞了，因為警方認為這個設備正在拍攝。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-16681630 |title=BBC News – The man who hears colour |accessdate=2020-02-19 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112041008/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-16681630 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/NeilHarbisson/status/74767773393354752 |title=Twitter / @NeilHarbisson: Eyeborg broken by police a … |accessdate=2020-02-19 |archive-date=2020-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522160742/https://twitter.com/NeilHarbisson/status/74767773393354752 |dead-url=no }}</ref>對此，哈維森提出警方對他造成身體上的傷害，而不是對個人財產的損害，因為他認為天線是人體的一部分。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/NeilHarbisson/status/74669760691974144 |title=Twitter / @NeilHarbisson: Secret police have just br … |accessdate=2020-02-19 |archive-date=2020-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522161006/https://twitter.com/NeilHarbisson/status/74669760691974144 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 協同合作 ==
